				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="FlipFour" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>FlipFour is an innovative approach to creating a new four-in-a-row game with great game play, but using just 4 pieces per player (i.e. the absolute minimum number of pieces).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;MATERIALS&amp;#10;&amp;#10;4 white FlipFlop pieces, 4 black FlipFlop pieces and a 5&amp;times;5 board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;FlipFlop pieces have a '+' on one side and a 'x' on the other.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;RULES&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Initial Setup&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The board starts empty. Decide which player plays white; the other plays black. Take all 4 pieces of your color.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Goal&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to get all 4 of her pieces in an orthogonal or diagonal line wins (It does not matter whether her 4 pieces are +, &amp;times;, or some of each).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to Play&amp;#10;&amp;#10;White plays first. Players take turns either placing or moving one of their own pieces on the board, following the rules below:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1) When you place a new piece, it must be placed on an empty space, but you can choose whether to place it +side-up or &amp;times;-side-up.&amp;#10;2) When you move a piece, + moves orthogonally, and &amp;times; moves diagonally, as the lines suggest. Move your piece any distance to an empty space.&amp;#10;3) Pieces can jump over other pieces as long as the destination space is empty.&amp;#10;4) After you move your piece, you must flip it over (+ becomes &amp;times;; &amp;times; becomes +).&amp;#10;5) You are welcome to move your pieces before all of you pieces are on the board. &amp;#10;6) Passing is not allowed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
